# Template Entry Rule

This repository uses a `.cursor` workflow template.

Before substantial work:

- Read `.cursor/README.md`.
- Read relevant files in `.cursor/project/`.
- Treat `.cursor/rules/` as reusable Cursor behavior.
- Treat `.cursor/core/` as reusable detailed workflow templates.
- Treat `.cursor/project/` as repository-specific overlay.
- Treat `.cursor/packs/` as technology-specific guidance.

Default behavior:

- Put coding style in `.cursor/project/CODING_CONVENTIONS.md`.
- Put folder/module/ownership structure in `.cursor/project/STRUCTURE.md`.
- Put build/test/lint commands in `.cursor/project/TOOLING.md`.
- Put phase/task plans in `.cursor/project/WORKFLOW.md`.
- Do not move repository-specific rules into reusable rules.
- For detailed role behavior, use `.cursor/core/agents/`.
- For dry-run, orchestration, resume, status, stop, or validation behavior, use
  `.cursor/core/commands/`.
- For event, progress, mailbox, heartbeat, and checkpoint formats, use
  `.cursor/core/protocols/`.
